\frac{dy}{dx}
(x,y)=(3,-1)
x^2+y^2+4x+8y+3=0
2x+2y\frac{dy}{dx}+4+8\frac{dy}{dx}=0
\dfrac{dy}{dx}(2y+8)=-2x-4
\dfrac{dy}{dx}=\dfrac{-2x-4}{2y+8}
\dfrac{dy}{dx}=-\dfrac{x+2}{y+4}
\dfrac{dy}{dx}=-\dfrac{5}{3}
y-y_1=m(x-x_1)
y-1=-\dfrac{5}{3}(x-3)
y-1=-\dfrac{5x-15}{3}
y-1=-\dfrac{5x}{3}+5
y=-\dfrac{5x}{3}+6
